{# Anthology Atlas — proof of concept (#1124). Soft launch: EN only, noindex,
   unlinked from navigation, excluded from the sitemap (eleventyExcludeFrom
   Collections drops it from collections.all, which the sitemap iterates) and
   from site search (data-pagefind-ignore below). The graph is the real
   /data/anthology-atlas.json, projected from paperIndex.js at build time.
   Sibling of the NetSec Atlas (people); this one maps papers. #}
<div class="atlas-shell" data-pagefind-ignore="all">
  <a class="atlas-back" href="/anthology.html">&larr; The Anthology</a>
  <div class="atlas-masthead">
    <h1>Anthology Atlas</h1>
    <span class="atlas-proto-pill">Prototype</span>
  </div>
  <p class="atlas-lede">A map of the <strong>European Security Studies Anthology</strong> — every paper presented at an EISS conference or workshop since 2017, drawn toward the <strong>research themes</strong> it touches. Papers on more than one theme settle between hubs, so the thematic bridges of the field become visible; each dot is coloured by its <strong>edition year</strong>, so the map doubles as a view of the field over time. Filter by year or spotlight a theme with the chips. Hover a paper for its title, authors and panel; click through to its Anthology page where one exists. Everything here is generated from the same data behind the <a href="/anthology.html">Anthology</a>.</p>

  <div class="atlas-stats" id="atlas-stats" aria-label="Anthology statistics"></div>

  <div class="atlas-controls" id="atlas-years" role="group" aria-label="Filter by edition year">
    <span class="lbl">Editions</span>
    <!-- year chips injected by anthology-atlas.js -->
  </div>
  <div class="atlas-controls" id="atlas-themes" role="group" aria-label="Spotlight a research theme">
    <span class="lbl">Themes</span>
    <!-- theme hub chips injected by anthology-atlas.js -->
  </div>

  <div class="atlas-stage">
    <canvas id="atlas-canvas" aria-label="Force-directed map of the European Security Studies Anthology: every paper drawn toward the research themes it touches, coloured by edition year. The same papers are available as a filterable list on the Anthology page."></canvas>
    <div class="atlas-card" id="atlas-card" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="atlas-legend" id="atlas-legend">
    <span><span class="sw sw-page"></span>has an Anthology page</span>
    <span><span class="sw sw-nopage"></span>programme entry only (no page yet)</span>
    <span><span class="sw sw-ring sw-prize"></span>Best Paper Prize</span>
    <span><span class="sw sw-pub"></span>published version on record</span>
    <span>drag a theme hub to rearrange the map</span>
  </div>
</div>

<script src="{{ '/assets/js/anthology-atlas.js' | bust }}" defer></script>
